       Right there, Phil.

03:08.154 --> 03:09.888
       ( gunshots firing )

03:11.257 --> 03:12.324
                Get 'em, Juju !

03:12.425 --> 03:13.458
         Fetch up, Ruby.

03:13.526 --> 03:14.993
      Hey, look out there.

03:15.061 --> 03:16.261
         I knocked down
           two of them

03:16.329 --> 03:17.829
           and my dog
        didn't even move.

03:17.897 --> 03:19.831
       Ruby, were you even
       paying attention ?

03:19.899 --> 03:21.833
             ( Jase )
             Si, I don't think
             that dog likes you.

03:21.901 --> 03:23.035
          What are you
         talking about ?

03:23.136 --> 03:25.837
    Silas Robertson and dogs,

03:25.905 --> 03:27.940
           they don't
         bond too well.

03:28.041 --> 03:29.975
 I don't know what you over here
     breathing so hard for.

03:30.076 --> 03:31.443
     You ain't done nothing.

03:31.544 --> 03:33.145
            ( Phil )
    You can have a prize lab

03:33.246 --> 03:35.113
  that's trained in every way,

03:35.181 --> 03:36.682
         but they start
      running with old Si,

03:36.783 --> 03:39.218
     they forget everything
      they've ever learned.

03:39.285 --> 03:40.352
    Takes about ten minutes.

03:40.453 --> 03:41.687
       ( dog whimpering )

03:41.788 --> 03:43.188
   No, you can't have my tea,
              Rube.

03:43.256 --> 03:44.456
          No tea, Rube.

03:44.557 --> 03:46.124
   Hey, there's nothing better

03:46.192 --> 03:48.060
        than hunting with
       a man and his dog.

03:48.161 --> 03:49.061
          Eh-eh-eh-eh.

03:49.162 --> 03:50.462
           Nope, nope.

03:50.563 --> 03:52.231
        Hey... you stay.

03:52.332 --> 03:54.233
       That's a bond that
        cannot be broken.

03:54.334 --> 03:55.968
      Nope, Rube, Rube, no.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.803
            But, hey,
   something ain't right here.

03:57.904 --> 03:59.538
    When are you gonna get in
        on the hunt here

03:59.639 --> 04:01.206
           instead of
    sitting there, looking ?

04:01.274 --> 04:02.307
         Hey, look here.

04:02.375 --> 04:03.742
          You're a dog.

04:03.843 --> 04:05.377
   Why do you think they have
            the term,

04:05.478 --> 04:06.778
     "working like a dog" ?

04:06.846 --> 04:08.580
( Phil )
Hey, right here,
right here, coming.

04:08.648 --> 04:10.449
              Here he comes, Si.
           I see him,
      I see him, I see him.

04:10.550 --> 04:11.650
       ( gunshots firing )

04:11.751 --> 04:13.652
                        Uh-oh !

04:13.753 --> 04:15.120
        God, got a piece
          of that one.

04:15.188 --> 04:16.622
         Fetch up here,
            come on.

04:16.723 --> 04:18.457
              Nope, she's going
              on the dove's, Si.

04:18.558 --> 04:19.558
        Good girl, Ruby.

04:19.659 --> 04:20.959
       All right, come on.

04:21.027 --> 04:22.127
        Ruby, fetch up !

04:22.195 --> 04:23.829
                       Uh-oh.
            Come on.

04:23.930 --> 04:26.565
     I have to say that dog
     won't bring it back to you.

04:26.666 --> 04:28.634
  ( laughing )

04:28.735 --> 04:30.435
       Personality issue.

04:30.503 --> 04:31.770
        I've had it with
           this thing.

04:31.838 --> 04:33.472
           Hey, she's
       just rubbing it in.

04:33.573 --> 04:35.474
      Ruby, fetch up here,
            come on.

04:35.575 --> 04:36.975
                  ( Jase )
                  That dog just
                  don't like Si.

04:37.043 --> 04:38.977
     This dog is defective.

04:39.045 --> 04:40.979
        I gotta find out
   if I can return this thing.

04:41.047 --> 04:42.681
               No dogs like Si.

04:42.782 --> 04:44.783
      I'm fixing to retire
          that heifer.

04:44.851 --> 04:46.852
         They smell 'em
         and they get bad vibes.

04:49.956 --> 04:51.290
               ( Willie )
               What coat is it ?

04:51.391 --> 04:52.658
That brown one.

04:52.759 --> 04:54.192
The one I got you
a couple months ago.

04:54.294 --> 04:55.427
                     Oh, yeah.

04:55.495 --> 04:57.195
                     Oh... yep.

04:59.966 --> 05:01.066
                      Ooh.

05:01.134 --> 05:02.100
         Is this mine ?

05:02.201 --> 05:03.669
That's yours.

05:03.770 --> 05:05.704
         Korie, did you leave it
         in the car too long ?

05:05.772 --> 05:08.206
I don't think a sports coat
can shrink, Willie.

05:08.308 --> 05:10.542
         Well... it has shrunk.

05:10.610 --> 05:12.377
           ( Willie )
          Korie's been
   doing this a lot recently.

05:12.445 --> 05:14.112
 She shops at these fancy stores

05:14.213 --> 05:16.548
     that sell clothes for,
   like, little European men.

05:16.616 --> 05:17.582
         They don't fit.

05:17.684 --> 05:19.685
                It's too tight.

05:19.786 --> 05:21.753
           ( Willie )
    She keeps saying they're
  the same size she always buys

05:21.854 --> 05:23.955
      but that's obviously
          not the case.

05:24.057 --> 05:25.290
 Let me button it.

05:25.358 --> 05:26.591
   Well...

05:26.693 --> 05:27.893
            Should I lay down ?

05:27.994 --> 05:29.394
I don't think that's
gonna help.

05:29.495 --> 05:31.263
          Korie, I can't do
          any of my dance moves.

05:32.632 --> 05:34.599
           See, when I go low--
           I can't even go low.

05:34.701 --> 05:37.102
Well, I mean, if you
want to lose a few pounds,

05:37.170 --> 05:38.537
you can come to yoga
with me.

05:40.340 --> 05:41.907
             Yoga ?

05:42.008 --> 05:43.575
          Korie, that's what
          men call "stretching."

05:43.643 --> 05:44.910
       I don't mind losing
          some weight,

05:45.011 --> 05:46.044
           but I ain't
      gonna lose my pride.

05:46.145 --> 05:47.145
         I'm not going to yoga.

05:47.246 --> 05:48.146
               That's for girls.
    Willie.

05:48.247 --> 05:49.614
              I'm not doing it.

05:49.716 --> 05:50.749
    I just need a little bit
     of help to get me back

05:50.817 --> 05:52.117
     to my fighting weight.

05:52.185 --> 05:54.319
             I know how to lose
             weight the man way.

05:54.420 --> 05:56.722
        Luckily, I still
        have my permit...

05:56.823 --> 05:58.557
       for these two guns.

05:58.658 --> 05:59.958
Well, I think
you look good.

06:00.026 --> 06:01.293
              I love you, baby.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.734
    I think I can button it.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.204
     Korie, can you help me
    get out of this jacket ?

06:14.907 --> 06:16.375
           ( Miss Kay )
           Hey, baby, come here.

06:16.476 --> 06:18.143
           I'm cooking--
           You like me cooking ?

06:18.211 --> 06:19.478
            That's what you do.

06:19.579 --> 06:20.479
             You want to eat it,
             don't you ?

06:20.580 --> 06:21.480
( Jase )
Well, hey, Miss Kay.

06:21.581 --> 06:23.715
          Hey, Jase, hey, guys.

06:23.816 --> 06:26.651
                    J.J. is such
                    a good dog.

06:26.753 --> 06:28.420
            That's what she is.

06:28.488 --> 06:30.689
               Such a good dog.

06:30.790 --> 06:32.457
                     Oh, gon.

06:32.558 --> 06:34.192
                Hey, y'all wanna
                eat some rice ?

06:34.260 --> 06:35.527
           You don't like rice.

06:35.628 --> 06:36.995
            ( Phil )
     Miss Kay is a dog lover

06:37.096 --> 06:40.198
  and she will talk to them in
         a kind, loving,

06:40.266 --> 06:41.400
          motherly way.

06:41.467 --> 06:43.301
                 ( whimpering )

06:43.369 --> 06:45.704
     I just whip their butt.

06:45.805 --> 06:46.738
( Jase )
We got you some doves.

06:46.839 --> 06:48.006
                       Oh !

06:48.107 --> 06:49.808
                    I love 'em,
                    I love 'em.

06:49.909 --> 06:51.209
        Well, me and Phil
          got you some.

06:51.277 --> 06:53.078
           Si was just
    there for moral support.

06:53.179 --> 06:54.813
            Si, you couldn't hit
            the doves ?

06:54.881 --> 06:56.515
Oh, hey,
I killed four or five.

06:56.616 --> 06:58.917
I gotta go get me
a real hunting dog.

06:59.018 --> 07:01.486
Emphasis on "hunting."

07:01.554 --> 07:03.889
    You gotta find a dog that
     fits your personality,

07:03.990 --> 07:05.323
         like me, okay ?

07:05.391 --> 07:06.758
        I need to get me
      a natural-born killer

07:06.826 --> 07:08.293
    when it comes to hunting.

07:08.394 --> 07:10.162
    She said, let me show you
     what I think about you.

07:10.263 --> 07:11.730
          ( chomping )

07:11.831 --> 07:12.998
Hey, personality issue.

07:13.099 --> 07:14.332
             ( Si )
      All right, look here.

07:14.400 --> 07:16.768
   You gotta be well-groomed,
           handsome--

07:16.836 --> 07:18.136
        I gotta find one,

07:18.204 --> 07:19.971
         hey, that don't
       mind to take a nap

07:20.039 --> 07:21.506
     every once in a while.

07:21.574 --> 07:23.508
I gotta go find me
a good dog.

07:23.576 --> 07:25.677
               ( Miss Kay )
               I'll go with you,
               I love dogs.

07:25.778 --> 07:27.112
         I have a sense about--

07:27.213 --> 07:28.780
Dogs do love you.

07:28.848 --> 07:31.516
  To get Si a dog, you're gonna
       need a sixth sense

07:31.584 --> 07:32.951
      and maybe a seventh.

07:33.052 --> 07:35.587
         Si's definitely
     not the dog whisperer.

07:35.688 --> 07:36.988
         He scares them.

07:37.056 --> 07:38.824
                     I can find
                     a good dog.

07:38.925 --> 07:40.759
              Look how good J.J.
              and Bobo are.

07:40.860 --> 07:43.128
Kay, it don't take much
to lay on the couch.

07:43.229 --> 07:44.596
I got that down pat.

07:44.697 --> 07:45.997
            ( Jase )
  I mean, the last dog we had,

07:46.065 --> 07:47.833
   the first thing the dog did

07:47.934 --> 07:50.035
           was bite Si
       right on the wrist.

07:50.136 --> 07:52.170
        I mean, Si scares
          humans, too.

07:52.238 --> 07:54.139
          But they just
         don't bite him.

07:54.240 --> 07:55.707
        ( Miss Kay )
        Well, we'll go tomorrow.
 All right.

07:55.775 --> 07:57.676
   Try to find you a dog with
          a screw loose

07:57.777 --> 07:59.611
    so it matches the master.

08:07.687 --> 08:10.088
     Willie, we finally got them
     duck pickers.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.523
               We're caught up.

08:11.624 --> 08:13.258
    Good.

08:18.798 --> 08:20.065
    What ?

08:22.401 --> 08:23.535
          ( exhaling )

08:23.636 --> 08:24.603
           What are you doing ?

08:24.704 --> 08:26.004
Working out.

08:26.072 --> 08:27.806
         That's not working out.
 Yeah, it is.

08:27.907 --> 08:29.307
My arms are burning.

08:29.408 --> 08:31.710
              My eyeballs
              is what's burning.

08:34.046 --> 08:35.847
I just burned
40 calories right then.

08:35.914 --> 08:37.549
                 ( laughing )

08:37.616 --> 08:39.618
  I mean, I don't know whether
      to laugh at Willie...

08:39.719 --> 08:41.186
             or cry.

08:41.254 --> 08:44.856
      I feel like I have to
   laugh to keep from crying.

08:44.924 --> 08:46.224
Jase, I've determined

08:46.292 --> 08:48.226
that I'm gonna
drop a few pounds.

08:48.294 --> 08:50.795
          This is a terrible way
          to do that !

08:50.897 --> 08:53.064
           What if somebody
           sees you doing this ?

08:53.165 --> 08:54.933
Well, most people
knock, but--

08:55.001 --> 08:56.201
                 What is this ?

08:56.269 --> 08:57.602
   Sweat suit.

08:57.703 --> 09:00.739
         What is seen...
        cannot be unseen.

09:00.840 --> 09:03.408
       This is etched into
          my brain now.

09:03.476 --> 09:05.544
         I don't know if
  I feel sorrier for Willie...

09:05.645 --> 09:06.811
           or myself.

09:06.913 --> 09:08.647
                 You've given me
                 a visual image

09:08.748 --> 09:09.714
               that I'm gonna
               have to deal with

09:09.815 --> 09:11.316
           the rest of my life.

09:11.384 --> 09:12.817
     I'm gonna wake up
     in the middle of the night,

09:12.919 --> 09:14.619
                  seeing you...

09:14.720 --> 09:17.622
           doing this with some
           kind of spacesuit on.

09:17.723 --> 09:18.924
It's a sweat suit.

09:19.025 --> 09:21.927
              You need to let me
              help you.

09:23.496 --> 09:24.963
   I would rather put my hair
           in pigtails

09:25.031 --> 09:26.231
         and wear makeup

09:26.299 --> 09:27.933
     than take workout tips
           from Jase.

09:28.034 --> 09:29.100
    No.

09:29.201 --> 09:30.769
        You want to get in shape
        in a hurry ?

09:30.836 --> 09:32.103
              I'll show you
              just how to do it.

09:32.204 --> 09:33.905
        It's real, it's natural

09:34.006 --> 09:35.907
                 and it's manly.
    Jase--

09:36.008 --> 09:38.243
                  I know the way
                  out of this !

09:38.311 --> 09:40.445
 But if he can help me drop some
   wait before this reunion...

09:40.513 --> 09:42.347
                   Are you ready
                   to do this ?

09:42.415 --> 09:44.916
        ... give me some
 ponytail holders and lipstick.

09:45.017 --> 09:47.152
Yes, if you'll get out of
my office and quit yelling.
                    You ready ?

09:47.219 --> 09:48.787
              All right, deal !

09:48.854 --> 09:51.256
         Operation Little Willie
         is in full effect.

09:51.324 --> 09:52.591
That's a terrible name.

