             ( Si )
     Hey, this place has got
     all kinds of dogs here.

10:18.050 --> 10:20.385
        Golden terriers,
   they got wiener schnitzels,

10:20.453 --> 10:22.487
     Trans-Siberian huskies.

10:22.588 --> 10:24.556
      I think I'll find me
           a dog here.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.358
This one's got a beard.

10:26.425 --> 10:28.526
Si, this dog
looks like you.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.328
     Looks have got nothing
         to do with it.

10:30.429 --> 10:32.063
        It's all about--
         hey-- attitude.

10:32.164 --> 10:33.798
        Look at that one.

10:33.899 --> 10:35.700
   He's the king of the hill--
        I don't want him.

10:35.801 --> 10:38.003
    You don't want a dog who
      thinks he's too fancy

10:38.070 --> 10:39.971
          for the work
       you want him to do.

10:40.072 --> 10:41.072
      You know, if you get
        a dog like that,

10:41.173 --> 10:42.641
          hey, the next
         thing you know,

10:42.708 --> 10:44.976
     you'll both be getting
       matching pedicures.

10:45.077 --> 10:47.746
              Sit--
     that's what I thought.

10:47.813 --> 10:50.348
Si, you gotta bond
with him, you know ?
          You gotta bond
         with him, Kay ?

10:50.449 --> 10:51.783
               Yeah, of course.

10:51.884 --> 10:53.385
  They love me.

10:53.452 --> 10:54.653
         I know why they
            love you.

10:54.720 --> 10:55.754
                  'Cause I smell
                  like food.

10:55.821 --> 10:56.888
          That's right.

10:56.989 --> 10:58.256
           They always
         love the cook.

10:58.357 --> 11:00.125
                      Right.
       That's what it is.

11:00.192 --> 11:01.926
          ( Miss Kay )
      It's not always easy
         to match a dog

11:02.028 --> 11:03.395
   with someone's personality,

11:03.462 --> 11:05.330
       especially somebody
            like Si.

11:05.431 --> 11:06.598
           ( dogs barking )
      Hey !

11:06.666 --> 11:08.800
          Settle down out there,
          all right.

11:08.901 --> 11:11.002
          If a dog had
        Si's personality,

11:11.103 --> 11:13.638
      it'd be old, cranky,
             mangy,

11:13.739 --> 11:15.073
          lazy, stinky.

11:15.174 --> 11:16.508
             ( Si )
       Hey, you won't do.

11:16.575 --> 11:19.010
     I would never get a nap
      with you around, son.

11:19.111 --> 11:20.945
          ( Miss Kay )
  Basically, if Si were a dog,

11:21.013 --> 11:22.847
   we'd have to put him down.

11:22.948 --> 11:25.083
         Hey, can we take one of
         these for a test run ?

11:25.184 --> 11:27.118
      Sure, we can take one
         for a test run.

11:27.219 --> 11:28.420
             ( Si )
         Hey, look here.

11:28.487 --> 11:31.256
    A dog is just like a car
          or a mattress

11:31.323 --> 11:32.657
      or a tree, you know.

11:32.758 --> 11:34.926
       You gotta test 'em.

11:35.027 --> 11:35.960
      All right, let's see
      what we're gonna do.

11:36.028 --> 11:37.929
          Looking good.

11:38.030 --> 11:40.331
Oh, that is good.
     All right, all right,
     here we go, all right.

11:40.399 --> 11:41.599
            Whoop...

11:43.302 --> 11:44.936
Good luck with that.

11:45.037 --> 11:46.337
                 I've never seen
                 her do that.

11:46.405 --> 11:47.839
     That's a defective dog.

11:47.940 --> 11:49.307
            Well, let's go look
            at some other dogs.

11:49.408 --> 11:50.375
We'll find one, Si.

11:50.476 --> 11:52.043
                We'll find one.

11:52.144 --> 11:54.012
      Yeah, I'll bring DNA
     to you if that'll help.

11:59.852 --> 12:02.020
            ( Jase )
        You gotta harness
      the power of the gut.

12:02.121 --> 12:04.122
( Jep )
Use inertia to your
advantage, come on.

12:04.223 --> 12:05.924
You got it.

12:06.025 --> 12:07.726
There it is.
           There you go.

12:07.793 --> 12:08.960
          You feel it ?

12:09.061 --> 12:11.262
        Why exactly am I cutting
        your firewood ?

12:11.330 --> 12:14.733
    Because I'm training you
        to get in shape.

12:14.800 --> 12:17.736
          I have chosen
     the perfect workout...

12:17.803 --> 12:19.070
           for Willie.

12:19.171 --> 12:20.238
          Lookee there.

12:20.339 --> 12:21.439
           Strike one.

12:21.540 --> 12:23.575
            I was in
    the best shape of my life

12:23.676 --> 12:25.810
       when I cut firewood
          for a living.

12:25.878 --> 12:28.046
    The more swinging you do,

12:28.147 --> 12:30.148
         the more carbs
         you're losing.

12:30.249 --> 12:33.384
    The greatest lesson that
   I learned hauling firewood

12:33.452 --> 12:35.220
       was that if you can
       find somebody else

12:35.321 --> 12:37.589
          to do this...

12:37.690 --> 12:38.790
             do it.

12:38.891 --> 12:40.158
                    This sucks.

12:40.259 --> 12:41.760
       Look, if you don't
          get in shape,

12:41.827 --> 12:44.562
         you're gonna be
     the butt of all jokes.

12:44.630 --> 12:47.298
I sure hope that ax doesn't slip
     and hit you in the gut.

12:47.366 --> 12:48.833
           'Cause then
     gravy's gonna come out.

12:48.901 --> 12:52.237
   ( laughing )

12:52.338 --> 12:54.038
             That's real funny.

12:54.106 --> 12:55.406
     Every time you back up,

12:55.474 --> 12:57.175
       we want the beeping
            to stop.

12:57.276 --> 12:59.144
( laughing )

12:59.245 --> 13:01.379
          How does insulting me
          help me lose weight ?

13:01.447 --> 13:02.847
       This is motivation.

13:02.915 --> 13:04.482
               I'm picturing all
               y'alls faces

13:04.550 --> 13:05.517
                   on the top
                   of this wood.

13:05.618 --> 13:07.352
          That's my motivation.

13:07.453 --> 13:10.488
 I know that reunions are about
  living your high school days,

13:10.556 --> 13:13.358
  but doing Jase's chores while
  he and Jep are sitting around

13:13.459 --> 13:15.727
         cracking jokes
   is not what I had in mind.

13:15.828 --> 13:17.529
                 What if I just
                 go into a gym ?

13:17.630 --> 13:18.730
           ( sighing )

13:18.831 --> 13:20.865
       You have got to be
           kidding me.

13:20.933 --> 13:23.201
        That's why people
        go to gyms, to work out.

13:23.302 --> 13:24.502
         Wear the little
          shorty-shorts

13:24.570 --> 13:26.504
           and prance
        around in a gym ?

13:26.572 --> 13:28.006
            ( Jase )
      When you're in a gym,

13:28.107 --> 13:30.275
      you're getting up on
       a stationary bike--

13:30.376 --> 13:31.776
              why ?

13:31.844 --> 13:33.545
   You're not going anywhere.

13:33.646 --> 13:34.579
        You got all this.

13:34.680 --> 13:36.181
       This is God's gym.

13:36.282 --> 13:40.585
        When I work out,
       I'm working out...

13:40.686 --> 13:41.886
              side.

13:41.954 --> 13:44.222
          Plus, I need
        my firewood cut.

13:44.323 --> 13:46.124
     I'm telling you, you're
        looking slimmer.

13:46.225 --> 13:47.892
      Don't you feel good ?

13:47.960 --> 13:49.727
                   No, I don't.

13:49.829 --> 13:51.429
             Uh-oh !

13:51.497 --> 13:53.364
          ( chuckling )

13:53.465 --> 13:54.766
            Man down.

13:54.867 --> 13:55.767
                   I'm done.

13:55.868 --> 13:57.168
         Come on, Will.

13:57.236 --> 13:58.436
          It's just one
          little knot.

13:58.504 --> 14:00.171
            You gotta
       get mad at the knot

14:00.239 --> 14:02.774
     and say, "Hey, I'm not
     gonna let you beat me."

14:02.875 --> 14:04.509
      You know why you hurt
           your back ?

14:04.610 --> 14:07.812
        'Cause you hadn't
  been doing this in 20 years.

14:07.880 --> 14:09.147
    You want Martin to rub it
          out for you ?

14:09.248 --> 14:10.348
( Jep )
Give him
a rubdown, Martin.

14:10.416 --> 14:12.217
             ( Martin )
             No, no, no, no, no.

14:12.318 --> 14:14.786
      He don't pay me to rub his
      back, that's for sure.

14:14.887 --> 14:17.655
       Let that back pain
       send you a message.

14:17.756 --> 14:18.656
         "Hey, Willie...

14:18.757 --> 14:20.792
            put down
        the bacon bits."

14:20.893 --> 14:22.227
    He didn't even get to finish
    the second part,

14:22.328 --> 14:23.561
                  stacking it.

14:23.629 --> 14:25.697
            That works them legs
            and the buttocks.

14:25.798 --> 14:26.731
                  You want to
                  get in shape ?

14:26.799 --> 14:28.032
No, I'm busy.

14:28.133 --> 14:30.068
This tea is not gonna
drink itself, Jase.

14:30.169 --> 14:31.402
                      Well...

14:31.503 --> 14:33.805
              Reed, Cole,
              got a job for you.

14:40.646 --> 14:42.580
            ( woman )
 Toes together, knees out wide,

14:42.648 --> 14:43.882
     and push your bum back
       towards your heels.

14:43.983 --> 14:45.083
          Breathe in--

14:45.184 --> 14:46.084
            Come on,
    lift your bum up, Willie.

14:46.185 --> 14:47.218
          Send it up to
            the sky.

14:47.286 --> 14:48.920
              Out.

14:49.021 --> 14:50.755
           ( Willie )
          I know I said
     I would never do yoga,

14:50.823 --> 14:52.490
      but, hey, after that
         day with Jase,

14:52.558 --> 14:55.293
    it's time to find a more
 relaxing way to get into shape.

14:55.394 --> 14:57.395
( woman )
Breathe in, down dog.

14:57.463 --> 14:58.496
           ( Willie )
        What can I say ?

14:58.564 --> 14:59.764
   When the going gets tough,

14:59.832 --> 15:01.799
       the tough strap on
          camo tights.

15:01.901 --> 15:03.234
( woman )
Breath in.
           Down dog means your--

15:03.302 --> 15:05.003
                  Make your body
                  like a "V."

15:05.104 --> 15:06.137
                   There you go.
       That ain't nothing
           like a dog.

15:06.205 --> 15:07.739
       Breathe in.

15:07.840 --> 15:10.942
      Willie has absolutely
    no idea how hard yoga is.

15:11.043 --> 15:12.443
       The dog does this,
           he's sick.

15:12.544 --> 15:14.913
Bring your
toes together.

15:15.014 --> 15:18.016
            I'm gonna
     enjoy seeing him sweat.

15:18.117 --> 15:19.183
    Up dog.

15:19.285 --> 15:20.652
             Up dog.

15:20.753 --> 15:22.220
Left foot forward,
Warrior I.

15:23.756 --> 15:25.256
           ( Willie )
        They should give
        these poses names

15:25.324 --> 15:28.793
      that reflect reality,
      like "spine snapper."

15:28.861 --> 15:30.528
  Where are we--
           Hold onto the straps,
           Willie.

15:30.596 --> 15:32.030
        Lift your chest.
                   There you go.

15:32.131 --> 15:34.299
Why don't you put
an apple in my mouth, too ?

15:34.400 --> 15:35.333
     Or "wheelchair-bound."

15:35.401 --> 15:36.968
            ( woman )
        Bridge or wheel.

15:37.036 --> 15:38.436
  You can come into a back bend
         if you'd like.

15:38.504 --> 15:39.837
         Put your hands
          by your ears.

15:39.939 --> 15:41.773
       Go up, lift, lift.
    ( Willie )
    Oh Lord, no.

15:41.874 --> 15:43.207
Y'all got a bridge,
I got a ditch.

15:43.309 --> 15:45.009
    Or "humanly impossible."

15:45.110 --> 15:47.712
            ( woman )
    If anybody wants to take
    headstand here, you can.

15:47.780 --> 15:49.047
Uh-uh, that ain't
happening.

15:49.148 --> 15:50.615
          I'm about to
       create my own pose.

15:50.683 --> 15:51.916
          ( sneezing )

15:51.984 --> 15:53.284
        "Dying fat man."

15:53.352 --> 15:54.719
          Breathe in, reach up.

15:54.787 --> 15:56.220
I'm-- I got
the breathing in.

15:56.322 --> 15:58.056
             Okay.
That's happening
naturally.

15:58.157 --> 15:59.357
            Release.

15:59.425 --> 16:01.259
   ( exhaling )

16:01.327 --> 16:03.428
         Let's come into
           happy baby.

16:05.164 --> 16:06.364
       Let's rock a little
         back and forth.

16:06.432 --> 16:07.532
          Who comes up
       with these words ?

16:08.801 --> 16:10.702
Korie, look how
ridiculous this is.

16:10.803 --> 16:11.769
            Hey, Mom.

16:11.870 --> 16:13.104
                 Oh, hey, baby.

16:13.172 --> 16:14.372
              Come on in,
              we're almost done.

16:14.440 --> 16:15.873
             Bella, look at this
             happy baby.

16:18.610 --> 16:19.844
   Phil...

16:19.945 --> 16:21.779
I thought Kay was
picking up Bella for me.

16:21.880 --> 16:23.915
         What y'all got
          going here ?
                 Oh, my Lord.

16:24.016 --> 16:26.417
           ( Willie )
 There's a lot of words I would
      use to describe this.

16:26.518 --> 16:28.286
   "Happy" is not one of them.

16:28.387 --> 16:29.854
                       ( Korie )
                       Oh.
Phil, it's not
what it looks like.

16:31.323 --> 16:32.223
            ( Phil )
             Danger.

16:32.324 --> 16:35.059
   ( imitating alarm beeping )

16:35.160 --> 16:36.260
      Red lights blinking.

16:36.328 --> 16:37.628
      Phil !

16:37.696 --> 16:40.064
        What in the world
    has happened to my boy ?

16:40.165 --> 16:41.332
       Dad !

16:41.433 --> 16:42.700
            ( Phil )
            Yuppies.

16:42.801 --> 16:44.435
   Oh, my God.

16:44.536 --> 16:46.304
I'm never gonna
hear the end of this.

16:46.405 --> 16:47.605
I'm not a happy baby.

16:51.810 --> 16:53.711
             ( Jase )
             I can't believe you
             bought that dog.

16:53.812 --> 16:56.314
             ( Si )
       Hey, don't badmouth
           my dog now.

16:56.415 --> 16:57.982
That's some hairdo there.

16:58.083 --> 17:00.218
       Hey, he ain't in no
   beauty contest, all right ?

17:00.319 --> 17:02.153
                Si, you've just
                gone slap crazy.

17:02.254 --> 17:03.321
               No.

17:03.422 --> 17:05.790
           Si, that's a poodle.

17:05.891 --> 17:06.858
              Hey.

17:06.959 --> 17:08.126
             I know.

17:08.193 --> 17:10.028
       Look at the statue
         on this thing.

17:10.095 --> 17:13.164
        I mean, he's got
 "killer" written all over him.

17:13.265 --> 17:15.165
               You're more blind
               than I thought.

17:15.267 --> 17:17.734
     Hey, poodles are one of
the best hunting dogs there are,

17:17.803 --> 17:19.237
      everybody knows that.

17:19.338 --> 17:22.807
That dog there was
bred for a fancy person.

17:22.907 --> 17:25.742
    And by the way, poodles,
 they don't give a rat's behind

17:25.810 --> 17:27.545
     about what other people
        think about 'em.

17:27.646 --> 17:29.647
        Hey, guess what ?
          Just like me.

17:29.748 --> 17:32.350
      That's what old women have
      and people of royalty.

17:32.451 --> 17:34.819
       Well, just call me
             Prince.

17:34.920 --> 17:36.587
            You know,
        what can I say ?

17:36.655 --> 17:39.190
     Si's dog... ridiculous.

17:39.291 --> 17:40.691
         I mean, the dog
         has got style.

17:40.759 --> 17:42.126
          Embarrassing.

17:42.194 --> 17:43.227
               I've never seen
               anything like it.

17:43.295 --> 17:44.929
             Stupid.

17:45.030 --> 17:46.831
  This sucker is a hunting dog
      now, I'm telling you.

17:46.932 --> 17:48.966
       Sometimes I really
       think he is insane.

17:49.034 --> 17:50.835
I tell you one thing,
he got a set of "cods"

17:50.936 --> 17:54.105
on him that would make old
Arnold Schwarzenegger blush.

17:54.206 --> 17:56.240
          He's all man,
     don't ever doubt that.

17:56.308 --> 17:57.942
      With a haircut like that,

17:58.043 --> 17:59.944
           he better have
           a set of cods on him.

18:00.045 --> 18:01.846
        I guarantee you.
                'Cause he's
                gonna need 'em.

18:01.947 --> 18:04.115
    Elvis had a hairdo, too,
      and look how he done.

18:05.384 --> 18:06.784
                    ( laughing )
            Hey.

18:06.852 --> 18:07.819
           Is that your logic ?

18:07.920 --> 18:09.353
   If we ever kill any doves,

18:09.421 --> 18:11.456
      y'all gonna take back
       all these bad words

18:11.557 --> 18:13.024
           y'all been
      talking about my dog.

18:13.125 --> 18:15.293
Uh-oh,
we got one that's blind.

18:15.394 --> 18:17.328
     He's leaning, he's leaning,
     he's leaning.

18:17.396 --> 18:18.563
                      Try him.

18:19.965 --> 18:21.766
      All right, fetch up,
           Coot, back.

18:23.068 --> 18:24.368
                Oh my goodness.

18:24.470 --> 18:27.271
            That dog is going to
            get that dove.

18:27.339 --> 18:29.807
            ( Jase )
       The poodle actually

18:29.875 --> 18:32.610
        retrieves doves.

18:32.678 --> 18:34.312
( Phil )
If I hadn't have seen it,
I wouldn't have believed it.

18:34.413 --> 18:35.947
            Good boy.

18:36.048 --> 18:38.683
I'll never badmouth another
poodle as long as I live.

18:38.784 --> 18:40.384
            ( Phil )
     We might all break out
        with the poodles

18:40.486 --> 18:42.086
          if we can get
     past the embarrassment

18:42.154 --> 18:44.355
   of having them ride in your
         truck with you.

18:44.423 --> 18:45.957
        Somebody sees you
    with a poodle, that's a--

18:46.058 --> 18:47.592
    Kind of a scary thought.

18:47.693 --> 18:50.361
       Good work, killer,
            good dog.

18:50.429 --> 18:53.898
     That right there, hey,
   that's a Si Robertson dog.

18:53.966 --> 18:56.134
              ( Jase )
              I think Si's found
              his soul mate.

18:56.235 --> 18:58.803
             ( Si )
       Old Mr. Fancypants
        ain't bad, Jase.

19:01.240 --> 19:02.240
( Bella )
Where's Mom ?

19:02.341 --> 19:03.441
She's taking forever.

19:03.542 --> 19:04.775
                 Hurry up, Mom.

19:04.877 --> 19:05.977
            ( Korie )
    All right, y'all ready ?

19:06.078 --> 19:07.778
        Yeah.
                        Yeah.

19:07.880 --> 19:09.580
             Whoa !

19:09.648 --> 19:10.982
             Mama !

19:11.083 --> 19:12.083
   You like it ?

19:12.184 --> 19:13.384
              Yeah.

19:13.452 --> 19:14.719
Do I still got it
after all these years ?

19:14.820 --> 19:16.087
          Yeah, you do.

19:16.188 --> 19:18.456
      Now let's see if Dad
          still has it.

19:18.557 --> 19:19.891
Come on, Willie.

19:19.992 --> 19:21.259
        Can't rush this.

19:21.360 --> 19:23.594
Oh, looking good,
looking good.

19:23.695 --> 19:26.264
 Well, it's come to my attention
     that since high school

19:26.365 --> 19:27.899
           I've put on
        a little weight.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.101
           No, not you, Dad.

19:30.202 --> 19:32.103
        Pipe down, Sadie.

19:32.204 --> 19:36.440
 So... I've been on a strenuous
        exercise program.

19:37.709 --> 19:39.810
           This jacket
       has become a symbol

19:39.912 --> 19:42.246
     of the new, thinner me.

19:42.347 --> 19:43.281
           This is it.

19:43.382 --> 19:44.849
      The moment of truth.

19:44.917 --> 19:45.950
       Let's hope it fits.

19:46.018 --> 19:47.185
All right, go for it,
Will.

19:47.286 --> 19:48.286
         Drumroll, Will.

19:50.489 --> 19:52.123
         A little help.
  All right.

19:53.659 --> 19:54.625
Let's see.

19:54.726 --> 19:56.494
 Ooh !
                       Yeah.

19:56.562 --> 19:58.629
Oh, and it
even buttons.

19:58.730 --> 20:00.631
            It does.
     Wow.

20:00.732 --> 20:03.034
      Holy crap, this thing
         actually fits ?

20:03.135 --> 20:04.368
That looks good.

20:06.138 --> 20:07.438
            You see ?

20:07.506 --> 20:09.874
    Hard work and dedication
       actually pays off.

20:09.942 --> 20:11.842
         And I still got
   a little room for dancing.

20:11.944 --> 20:13.477
Yeah, and you
look good.

20:13.579 --> 20:16.347
  A good wife will support her
     husband no matter what.

20:16.415 --> 20:18.216
Just as hot as you
were when I married you.

20:18.317 --> 20:19.650
                       Oh, man.

20:19.751 --> 20:21.485
            ( Korie )
 A great wife saves the receipt

20:21.587 --> 20:23.454
  and takes the jacket back for
        a bigger size...

20:23.522 --> 20:25.122
     when nobody's looking.

20:25.224 --> 20:26.190
        All right, kids,
         we're leaving.

20:26.291 --> 20:27.291
                        Bye !

